sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1763439
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: MaSp1 and MaSp2 12-mer block co-polymer under control of T7 promoter and RBS. Ratio of 2 MaSp1 to 1 MaSp2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinson Lam

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1763438
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: MaSp1 and MaSp2 12-mer block co-polymer in pSB1C3, no regulatory elements. Ratio of 2 MaSp1 to 1 MaSp2.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinson Lam
